<p>You can make a business more profitable by reducing costs, not by borrowing more than your revenues can service.</p>

<p>If you reduce costs and increase profitability you can then invest to grow, but constantly borrowing to service earlier debt while never turning a profit is a recipe for bankruptcy.</p>

<p>You can make a business more profitable by reducing costs, or a combination of cost cutting and efficiency gains.  However, you cannot grow a business by doing those.  You just end up getting swallowed up by a competitor, or completely outdone.</p>

